  "local_port": 42654,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Is there a way to for my Google Calendar to manage my Office 365 Exchange Cal that doesn't involve using the Subscribe Option?",
  "response": "To manage your Office 365 Exchange Calendar with Google Calendar without using the \"Subscribe\" option, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Add your Office 365 account to Google Calendar:**\n\n   - Open Google Calendar.\n   - Click on the gear icon in the top right corner and select \"Settings.\"\n   - In the left sidebar, click on \"Add calendar\" and then \"Add personal calendar.\"\n   - Click on \"Add account\" and enter your Office 365 email address.\n   - Follow the prompts to sign in to your Office 365 account and grant the necessary permissions.\n\n2. **Authorize Google Calendar to access your Office 365 Exchange Calendar:**\n\n   - After adding your Office 365 account, Google Calendar will prompt you to authorize access to your Exchange Calendar.\n   - Click on \"Allow\" to grant the necessary permissions.\n\n3. **Configure the Office 365 Exchange Calendar in Google Calendar:**\n\n   - Once your Office 365 account is added and authorized, you should see your Exchange Calendar appear in the \"Other calendars\" section on the left sidebar.\n   - Click on the three dots next to your Exchange Calendar and select \"Settings.\"\n   - In the \"Calendar Settings\" page, you can customize the calendar's name, color, and other preferences.\n\n4. **Create and manage events:**\n\n   - You can now create, edit, and delete events directly from Google Calendar, and these changes will sync with your Office 365 Exchange Calendar.\n   - When creating a new event, select your Office 365 Exchange Calendar from the \"Calendar\" dropdown menu.\n\nBy following these steps, you can effectively manage your Office 365 Exchange Calendar using Google Calendar without relying on the \"Subscribe\" option. This method allows for two-way synchronization, enabling you to create, edit, and delete events from either platform.\n\nKeep in mind that the exact steps and interface may vary slightly depending on your Google Calendar version and settings. If you encounter any issues during the setup process, consult Google's support documentation or contact their support team for assistance.",
